MESSAGE: car has been sitting for a long time and although i did pressure wash it before the pics were taken it still has some stains on the paint that should wash off. i have clear title and it is the early 99 production run 1.9l tdi; not the late 99 that would have been easy to find back when i started trying to fix it. the door bumper mouldings that are not pictured are in fact here; and in good condition. basically when i got this car the engine had no compression and i assumed the head gasket was blown; but it turned out to be a bad cracked piston rings that trashed the cylinder head chamber as well as the piston and scratched the cylinder wall. i had the block bored out; bought a new head; new set pistons with wrist pins and rings; full gasket/seal set; precise match head gasket; new head bolts; and a new timing set kit.  unfortunately i developed back problems and had to stop working for about 6 months; and that was a couple of years ago. now i just want to sell off this project and work on my boats. the body is easily worth $500 alone; it has decent paint; and other than a cut on the rear bumper cover; the car does not have any dents. it does not have alloy wheels; but i did run across a factory jetta trunk spoiler that i have put away here somewhere. the 5spd tranny is worth around $500 and engine parts like the turbo; injection pump; new pistons; and new head casting are worth around $1000 and all the engine parts have been kept in a dry shed.  these cars are still known for getting almost 50 mpg on the highway and this one was made long before all the hoopla about cheating on emissions tests.  call or email for detailed communication. it you choose to text once or twice fine; but i will not get involved in a long texting exchange as it is too time consuming compared to a simple phone call. the price is firm at $1500.

MESSAGE: up for sale is my 2001 vw jetta. its got the 2.0 i4 with a manual 5 speed. it has 221k miles but runs and drives great. the exterior is pretty rough; including a matte black fender; but no rust or anything like that.#it has a new front driver side strut (bilstein); new front passenger large lca bushing; new coil pack; new cps; new spark plugs (bosch platinum); and new bits in the interior that needed replaced. the glovebox is broken and wont latch closed; replacements are cheap and its an easy fix; just not a part i got around to. the doors do not lock because of the driver door lock actuator; $25 online and yet another easy fix. i just never left anything of value in the car. everything else works as it should; including the heated seats.#the abs and brake wear pad lights are on. the pads are fine; the abs works; this was due to my own stupidity. the strut i replaced in the front had kinked itself around the steering knuckle when it broke; making it difficult to remove. the abs sensor and brake pad sensor wires were victims of getting the strut separated from the steering knuckle.#it will need front tires. a completely done front driver strut and an lca bushing that stopped being one piece was causing some heavy alignment issues. i have fixed the problems; but not before the screwy alignment completely ate through the outsides of the tires. so theyre bald on the outer sides; and thus doesnt drive all that straight. $80 mounted and balanced for a decent used pair at the tire shop on washington way across the street from shell and jiffy lube.#finally; the engine has lifter tick. this is not at all detrimental. its had a lifter tick since i purchased it 8k miles ago. its just a little annoying more than anything. it can usually be fixed by cleaning out the lifters. still runs and drives fine.#it got an oil change the day i picked it up from my boss; and got one 5k miles later. both times with full synthetic valvoline and bosch filters. the previous owner replaced the water pump with one that has metal internals. looking for $700 obo
